{"article_id":"CPnGigWfPsCmL5lr","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Obamacare may not be fixed","depth":9},{"id":1,"text":"when promised .","depth":9},{"id":2,"text":"That ' s the implication of a bombshell story in The Washington Post Wednesday ,","depth":9},{"id":3,"text":"which says","depth":10},{"id":4,"text":"stubborn software problems are likely to hobble the federal online health insurance marketplace into early December and perhaps beyond .","depth":10},{"id":5,"text":"Right now the troubled HealthCare.gov site can ' t handle more than 20,000 to 30,000 users at a time ,","depth":10},{"id":6,"text":"according to Post reporters Amy Goldstein , Juliet Eilperin , and Lena H. Sun .","depth":10},{"id":7,"text":"That ' s about half its intended capacity .","depth":9},{"id":8,"text":"According to an unnamed official","depth":11},{"id":9,"text":"quoted in the story ,","depth":11},{"id":10,"text":"technical experts have concluded","depth":11},{"id":11,"text":"that this situation isn ' t getting better soon .","depth":11},{"id":12,"text":"This official says","depth":10},{"id":13,"text":"that those","depth":13},{"id":14,"text":"trying to fix the problems","depth":13},{"id":15,"text":"now believe","depth":12},{"id":16,"text":"that \" the only way","depth":14},{"id":17,"text":"for large numbers of Americans to enroll in the health-care plans soon","depth":14},{"id":18,"text":"is by using other means","depth":13},{"id":19,"text":"so that the online system isn ' t overburdened . \"","depth":12},{"id":20,"text":"President Obama likely winced","depth":7},{"id":21,"text":"when he saw this piece in his morning news feed .","depth":7},{"id":22,"text":"Back in October , Jeff Zients , the management expert","depth":9},{"id":23,"text":"brought in by the White House","depth":10},{"id":24,"text":"to rescue the troubled HealthCare.gov ,","depth":10},{"id":25,"text":"told reporters","depth":9},{"id":26,"text":"that the site would be working smoothly for the vast majority of users \" by the end of November . \"","depth":9},{"id":27,"text":"Perhaps that ' s a red line","depth":8},{"id":28,"text":"Mr. Zients should not have drawn .","depth":8},{"id":29,"text":"Now the administration faces the prospect","depth":9},{"id":30,"text":"of missing a deadline","depth":10},{"id":31,"text":"it imposed on itself .","depth":10},{"id":32,"text":"Or does it ?","depth":8},{"id":33,"text":"On the record , White House spokesfolks are pushing back against this report Wednesday morning .","depth":8},{"id":34,"text":"Administration communications official Jennifer Palmieri insisted to New York Magazine","depth":10},{"id":35,"text":"that fixing the site by the end of November is still a \" go . \"","depth":10},{"id":36,"text":"\" The website will be working well for a majority of users by Nov. 30 , \"","depth":10},{"id":37,"text":"Palmieri told the magazine ' s Jonathan Chait .","depth":10},{"id":38,"text":"So what ' s going on here ?","depth":7},{"id":39,"text":"Is this a big deal , or a tempest in a tea cup","depth":8},{"id":40,"text":"( green loose leaf ,","depth":9},{"id":41,"text":"hold the milk and sugar ) ?","depth":9},{"id":42,"text":"We ' d say","depth":8},{"id":43,"text":"its importantish .","depth":8},{"id":44,"text":"Missing the deadline could cause big political problems for the White House .","depth":8},{"id":45,"text":"If nothing else , the administration is positioning for a coming fight","depth":10},{"id":46,"text":"on what constitutes \" success \" in the next few weeks .","depth":10},{"id":47,"text":"In that context , the website ' s capacity becomes a crucial piece of information .","depth":9},{"id":48,"text":"The Post apparently has the techie viewpoint :","depth":6},{"id":49,"text":"It ' s still broken .","depth":7},{"id":50,"text":"But the administration may argue","depth":8},{"id":51,"text":"that things are much better","depth":11},{"id":52,"text":"than they were","depth":11},{"id":53,"text":"( true )","depth":10},{"id":54,"text":"and that therefore it ' s OK to make the somewhat arbitrary judgment","depth":10},{"id":55,"text":"that the website is \" fixed . \"","depth":10},{"id":56,"text":"As to the political situation , many Democrats are urging the Obama team to figure out a Plan B , and fast .","depth":6},{"id":57,"text":"Notable among them is ex-president Bill Clinton ,","depth":7},{"id":58,"text":"who said in an interview released Tuesday","depth":8},{"id":59,"text":"that the administration should ensure","depth":9},{"id":60,"text":"Americans can retain their current health policies","depth":11},{"id":61,"text":"if they wish","depth":11},{"id":62,"text":"\" even if it takes a change to the law . \"","depth":10},{"id":63,"text":"Some Democratic lawmakers are forging ahead by themselves .","depth":7},{"id":64,"text":"Sen. Mary Landrieu","depth":10},{"id":65,"text":"( D )","depth":10},{"id":66,"text":"of Louisiana has introduced legislation","depth":9},{"id":67,"text":"that would mandate insurance companies keep people on current plans","depth":9},{"id":68,"text":"if they want .","depth":9},{"id":69,"text":"Republicans , meanwhile , are seizing on this internal Democratic dissent as evidence","depth":8},{"id":70,"text":"that they ' ve been right all along about the nature of the Affordable Care Act .","depth":8},{"id":71,"text":"Clinton ' s comments \" signify a growing recognition","depth":9},{"id":72,"text":"that Americans were misled","depth":10},{"id":73,"text":"when they were promised that they could keep their coverage under President Obama ' s health care law , \"","depth":10},{"id":74,"text":"said Speaker of the House John Boehner","depth":10},{"id":75,"text":"( R )","depth":10},{"id":76,"text":"of Ohio .","depth":9},{"id":77,"text":"What the administration really does not want to happen here is for congressional Democrats to break and agree to some temporary fix , perhaps even a delay in the individual mandate ,","depth":5},{"id":78,"text":"which could make it harder to implement Obamacare down the road .","depth":5},{"id":79,"text":"Politics aside , the Nov. 30 deadline and continued website glitches may not be crucial in terms of the rate of ACA enrollment .","depth":3},{"id":80,"text":"That ' s because previous experience indicates","depth":4},{"id":81,"text":"that most Americans may wait until close to the deadline","depth":5},{"id":82,"text":"before signing up for new or expanded social programs .","depth":5},{"id":83,"text":"Get the Monitor Stories","depth":5},{"id":84,"text":"you care about","depth":5},{"id":85,"text":"delivered to your inbox .","depth":4},{"id":86,"text":"By signing up ,","depth":4},{"id":87,"text":"you agree to our Privacy Policy","depth":4},{"id":88,"text":"When Medicare ' s Part D prescription drug plan rolled out in the Bush presidency ,","depth":5},{"id":89,"text":"two-thirds of those","depth":8},{"id":90,"text":"who enrolled","depth":8},{"id":91,"text":"did so","depth":7},{"id":92,"text":"after coverage actually began on Jan. 1 , 2006 ,","depth":6},{"id":93,"text":"according to figures from market analysis firm Avalere Health .","depth":4},{"id":94,"text":"\" People are slow to purchase coverage","depth":6},{"id":95,"text":"when new programs begin ,","depth":6},{"id":96,"text":"and","depth":6},{"id":97,"text":"if past programs are any guide ,","depth":7},{"id":98,"text":"we expect","depth":8},{"id":99,"text":"most exchange participants will wait until after January 2014","depth":9},{"id":100,"text":"to enroll , \"","depth":9},{"id":101,"text":"said Avalere vice president Caroline Pearson in late October .","depth":4}],"relations":[{"parent":203,"left":184,"right":202,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":184,"left":180,"right":183,"relation":"evaluation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":180,"left":157,"right":179,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":157,"left":139,"right":156,"relation":"evaluation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":139,"left":123,"right":138,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":123,"l